definitions.definition: To direct a ship ; to superintend the steering of (a vessel); to watch the course of (a vessel) and direct the helmsman how to steer (especially through a channel , etc, rather than steer a compass direction).
examples: The pilot conned the ship safely into the harbor.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To direct a ship ; to superintend the steering of (a vessel); to watch the course of (a vessel) and direct the helmsman how to steer (especially through a channel , etc, rather than steer a compass direction).
